# Dependency Injection

ALL code MUST use Dependency Injection. Depend on abstractions, never concretions.

## NestJS (Server)

Use NestJS built-in DI container. Always inject via constructor with string tokens and interfaces.

### Standard Service DI

```typescript
interface IUserRepository {
  findById(id: string): Promise<User>
}

@Injectable()
class UserRepository implements IUserRepository {
  findById(id: string): Promise<User> { /* ... */ }
}

@Injectable()
class UserService {
  constructor(
    @Inject('IUserRepository') private readonly userRepo: IUserRepository,
  ) {}
}

@Module({
  providers: [
    { provide: 'IUserRepository', useClass: UserRepository },
    UserService,
  ],
})
export class UserModule {}
```

### LLM Provider DI via LlmModule

For LLM providers, use `LlmModule.register()` from `@primer-guidy/nest-shared`. Injection tokens MUST be defined in `src/tokens.ts` (NEVER in `app.module.ts`) to avoid circular dependencies:

```typescript
// src/tokens.ts — tokens separate from modules
export const LLM_GUARD = 'ILlmGuardProvider'
export const LLM_CURATION = 'ILlmCurationProvider'
```

```typescript
// app.module.ts — register tokens with model env vars
import { LlmModule } from '@primer-guidy/nest-shared'
import { LLM_GUARD, LLM_CURATION } from './tokens'

@Module({
  imports: [
    LlmModule.register([
      { token: LLM_GUARD, modelEnv: 'GUARD_MODEL', defaultModel: 'llama-guard3:8b' },
      { token: LLM_CURATION, modelEnv: 'CURATION_MODEL', defaultModel: 'llama3.1:8b' },
    ]),
  ],
})
export class AppModule {}
```

```typescript
// service.ts — inject by token, type by interface
import { Inject } from '@nestjs/common'
import type { ILlmProvider } from '@primer-guidy/llm-services'
import { LLM_GUARD } from '../../tokens'

@Injectable()
export class SafetyGuardService {
  constructor(@Inject(LLM_GUARD) private readonly guard: ILlmProvider) {}
}
```

`LlmModule.register()` is a `@Global()` dynamic module — registered tokens are available in all feature modules without re-importing. For full LLM DI patterns including multi-provider registration, model env resolution, adapter selection, and the port/adapter type system, see `llm-integration.mdc`.

## React (Web)

Use React Context as DI container. Services injected via providers.

```tsx
interface IAuthService {
  login(credentials: Credentials): Promise<User>
}

const AuthServiceContext = createContext<IAuthService | null>(null)

export const useAuthService = (): IAuthService => {
  const service = useContext(AuthServiceContext)
  if (!service) throw new Error('AuthService not provided')
  return service
}
```

Composition root (app entry / root route) is the ONLY place where `new` is allowed:

```tsx
// __root.tsx or providers — composition root only
<AuthServiceContext.Provider value={new AuthServiceImpl()}>
  {children}
</AuthServiceContext.Provider>
```

## Rules

- NEVER instantiate dependencies with `new` inside a class/component (except composition root)
- Composition root = app entry, root route, or provider wrappers
- EVERY service/repository MUST have a corresponding interface
- Test doubles (mocks) replace implementations via DI — no monkey-patching
- NestJS injection tokens MUST live in `src/tokens.ts` — NEVER in `app.module.ts` (prevents circular dependencies)
- LLM providers are injected via `@Inject(TOKEN)` with `ILlmProvider` type from `@primer-guidy/llm-services`
- For tests, create mocks manually and pass via constructor: `new Service(mockProvider as never)` — no NestJS testing module needed
